           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Ok I have received countless complaint emails lately in regards to signature graphics and images in posts.  The primary complaint was that many images through posts increase the overall table of the forum far beyond that of their viewing plane.  Which makes many users have to use the scroll bar to read some of the posts.<br /><br />I have noticed this lately as well but since i run in 1600 x 1200 it doesn't effect me nearly as often.<br /><br />I believe something should be done.  We can go about this in a few ways.<br /><br />1.  Limit signatures to text only with hyperlinks.  Allow people to post signature images, character images, etc to their member profile page.  Which would allow people's creativity to be showcased without interferring with the flow of the message board.  This would also help load times.<br /><br />2.  Inforce a strict height x width on all signature graphics.  This can be a problem at times b.c all signature images would have to be exactly that specification or they would display incorrectly.<br /><br />If you have any other suggestions the debate is open.  Please let me know if you vote for 1 or 2.  If you don't vote, you will not be able to complain once I change it <img src="images/argh.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br /><br /><br /><br />And have yourself a Vision-tastic day.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=613651">Craptastic Gear of the Vision</a></span id="msg"></font>
